02/10/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- EU security chief Javier Solana expressed strong support Wednesday (1 October) for the Belgrade-Pristina talks, scheduled to begin on 14 October in Vienna. In a letter to Kosovo Parliament Speaker Nexhat Daci, Solana said the priority is to create a multiethnic society in the province. Solana called for better implementation of UN Resolution 1244 and said talks would focus on technical issues. (B92, BBC, Tanjug - 01/10/03)
